  "texts": [
    "The core QK ⊤ multiplication is an ensemble of pairwise attention scores between each token in a sequence, which can be decomposed as vector operations:",
    "AFT (Zhai et al., 2021), alternately formulates",
    "where {w t,i } ∈ R T ×T is the learned pair-wise position biases, and each w t,i is a scalar.",
    "Inspired by AFT, RWKV takes a similar approach.",
    "However, for simplicity, it modifies the interaction weights so that it can be transformed into an RNN."
  ]
}